 achieved by an uninterpretable learning based method,\nnamely diffractive deep neural networks (D2NN). The proposed differentiable\nmicroscopy framework supplements the creative process of designing new optical\nsystems and would perhaps lead to unconventional but better optical designs.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Mon, 28 Mar 2022 17:53:06 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Wed, 13 Apr 2022 17:28:15 GMT"},{"version":"v3","created":"Fri, 2 Dec 2022 18:52:40 GMT"}],"update_date":"2022-12-05"}
